{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6c0d161c-fed8-4e7c-b5ad-7fef1a5a3b12","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped** (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e7093f69-6777-40fe-bdea-96b5be944b73","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":303,"requestId":"BD03:1A8D4E:1D03692:20B3630:6A07C4BD"},"id":"f941f749-1846-4545-9b36-164b7d8be299","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:13:39.876Z","parentId":"2f458314-94f5-4859-ad07-ed13564fa7c4"}
